        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 31 at 2:24PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 224 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Divide, or 21 miles west of Colorado Springs, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea to half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pikes Peak.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
